HEADWORD: Panicle
<hw>Pan"i*cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>panicula</ets> a tuft on plants, dim. of <ets>panus</ets> the
thread wound upon the bobbin in a shuttle; cf. Gr. <?/, <?/; prob. akin
to E. <ets>pane</ets>: cf. F. <ets>panicule</ets>. See 2d
<er>Pane</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A pyramidal form of
inflorescence, in which the cluster is loosely branched below and
gradually simpler toward the end.</def><-- Illustr. of a panicle -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

